Backpack Buddies
The Spirit of Faith Church would like to sponsor any student/family who may need help purchasing school supplies this fall. Any one who is interested in utilizing this program can contact Sarah Jensen at 350-4310. The appropriate information (girl or boy and grade level; the rest will stay anonymous) will be given to the church. They will purchase the appropriate items for your child/children. Sarah Jensen will then contact you for pick-up or delivery of the supplies before the school year starts.

High School Chorus students-If you have not already done so, please check out Mrs. Easton's Google Classroom for updates.
Elementary and Middle School/Jr. High students-Here are some musical websites for you to explore!

Aural Training- Creating Music Block Game‚Äìcreate a 3-note pattern and then listen to a variety of patterns to choose the one you created
http://creatingmusic.com/BlockGames/3x3/

Composers- Quia Composer Fun Concentration‚Äìmatch composer with a famous work
https://www.quia.com/cc/65804.html

Musical Instruments- Flying Instruments‚Äîa Tetris-like game with three levels‚Äìmatching by instrument family, by instrument, and by sound
http://www.musicgames.net/livegames/flyinginstruments/flyinginstruments1.htm

Notation- Funbrain The Piano Player‚Äìstaff and piano keys recognition
https://www.funbrain.com/games/the-piano-player

Symbols and Vocabulary- Quia Musical Elements Matching‚Äìmatch musical elements and their definitions
https://www.quia.com/mc/65624.html

post_text:
A quick message from your Superintendent.

As you know, we are facing an unprecedented public health crisis in our nation. We understand that in addition to education, our school provides a vital support to our community and closure will have a major impact on our families. We are currently waiting further instruction, guidance, and updated information from our state government.

To be prepared for an extended closure, the school staff is in the process of implementing a Home Delivery Plan for all students. This includes Elearning lessons, Homework Packets, and Sack Lunches delivered Door to Door. We will update everyone with the latest information as soon as possible.

For Coronavirus updates and information please visit:

https://doh.sd.gov/news/Coronavirus.aspx

Supt. Rod Weber

post_text:
January 9th 9:30am

OPEN TO THE PUBLIC TO ATTEND

The Destroy Illusions School Assembly is unique from any assembly you have ever had! The creative approach to touch on a variety of topics during one assembly has been proven by over 3 million students to be an effective way to challenge ALL the students in the audience. Tom Coverly gets to the root issues and will destroy the illusions and lies young people are believing and remind them of truth and reality. Students will leave the assembly having more self worth, wanting to respect others more, choosing integrity, character, desiring to make wiser choices, stand up against bullying, appreciate the gift of life and see their life with a new found purpose!

If Tom Coverly had to sum up his assembly in one word it would be, "RESPECT". He focuses on respecting yourself, your peers and those in authority.

It is a decorated toilet that will be going around town as a lawn decoration. It will be $10 to be removed from your lawn, and placed on a new lawn of your choice. You can call/text Emily Henriksen at 605-933-1102 or Dayna Rodriguez at 605-520-4544 and one of the NHS students will be there as quickly as possible to remove it, collect the $10 and take it to its next destination. NHS Students will knock on you door to collect funds. You can pay in cash or make checks out to the Woonsocket National Honor Society.

If you would like to purchase ‚ÄúInsurance‚Äù for an extra $5 to make sure the Lawn Decoration doesn‚Äôt return to your house, just let us know!
